Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.63,0:00:10.44,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,It appeared as though humanity \Nwould be destroyed by the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.02,0:00:19.29,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,But a single mage saved them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.37,0:00:31.59,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,He was called the Wizard King,\Nand he became a legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.01,0:00:37.76,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The list of Magic Knights who \Nmade it into the Royal Knights
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.76,0:00:39.26,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,was announced at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.63,0:00:44.60,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Zora, one of those who passed, arrived late.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.63,0:00:49.65,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Shiren Tium, Cob Portaport, and the \NCaptain of the Silver Eagles, Nozel Silva,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.65,0:00:53.09,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,were also added later on as support,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.09,0:00:55.65,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,making for a total of 20 Royal Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.11,0:00:58.99,flashback,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,We have no use for anything \Nother than victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.99,0:01:00.37,flashback,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,The Eye of the Midnight Sun is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.37,0:01:02.79,flashback,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,a terrorist organization that \Nthreatens the Clover Kingdom!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.21,0:01:07.83,flashback,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't take care of them ourselves, \Nthere will never be peace in our land!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.83,0:01:11.54,flashback,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,The Eye of the Midnight Sun's hideout
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.54,0:01:12.38,flashback,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,is located in...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.82,0:01:17.58,flashback,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,a floating dungeon within the strong \Nmagic region known as Gravito Stones!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.27,0:01:51.00,Ep Title,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Storming the Eye of the \NMidnight Sun's Hideout!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.02,0:02:52.52,sign_12339_133_Finnes_Calmreich,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}The Crimson Lion Kings' Headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.89,0:03:00.65,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,I thank you for coming, my rival!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.65,0:03:05.78,sign_10111_106_Venue_for_the_Ro,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}The Crimson Lion Kings' Headquarters\N{\fs30}Infirmary
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.14,0:03:05.78,top,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from my sister that you two \Npassed the Royal Knights Exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.78,0:03:09.61,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! We're finally gonna take \Ndown the Eye of the Midnight Sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.61,0:03:11.61,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving in three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.61,0:03:14.79,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,We're standing by in the royal capital \Nuntil then so information won't be leaked.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.21,0:03:16.69,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.69,0:03:17.55,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.55,0:03:18.35,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.35,0:03:19.83,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,How's Fuegoleon doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.83,0:03:22.26,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,He's still asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.91,0:03:26.14,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,We still don't know what happened \Nto him when he was captured
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.14,0:03:29.93,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,by the Eye of the Midnight Sun during \Ntheir attack on the royal capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:32.26,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever they did,\NI'm sure it was underhanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.50,0:03:37.19,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,Yet even then, my brother would just say...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.89,0:03:42.57,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,"The reason I was unable to defeat \Nthem was my own weakness."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.98,0:03:49.74,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,I will train even harder, \Ncatch up to all of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.74,0:03:50.66,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,and surpass you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.66,0:03:52.38,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Leopold...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.38,0:03:56.01,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I will get revenge for Captain Fuegoleon,\N no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.86,0:04:01.42,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Captain Fuegoleon didn't laugh at \Nmy dream to become the Wizard King.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.91,0:04:04.26,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,He even called me a rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.83,0:04:08.39,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,The reason I'm here right now \Nis because of Captain Fuegoleon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.21,0:04:10.39,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.91,0:04:13.31,flashback,Fuego,0000,0000,0000,,Being weak is nothing to be ashamed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.71,0:04:15.40,flashback,Fuego,0000,0000,0000,,However, staying weak is!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.40,0:04:20.15,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Those words helped me grow stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.29,0:04:25.99,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,Asta, Noelle, I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.99,0:04:28.95,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! For the sake of returning \Npeace to this country...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.33,0:04:31.95,main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,...we'll defeat the Eye of the Midnight Sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.11,0:04:39.37,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, let's fight together, Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.37,0:04:41.30,main,Leo,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.30,0:04:42.10,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.10,0:04:43.08,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,We'll come by again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.17,0:04:56.22,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I hope Captain Fuegoleon \Nand Finral both wake up soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.02,0:04:58.15,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.46,0:05:01.16,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,The eerie feeling I got from that mana...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.16,0:05:04.15,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,The Eye of the Midnight \NSun might be behind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.50,0:05:07.07,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,We have to defeat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.07,0:05:08.34,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.23,0:05:13.06,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,But something's been bugging me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.06,0:05:14.08,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.08,0:05:17.07,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,You remember what that hairy gorilla said?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.86,0:05:20.17,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason, they can't forgive us, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.65,0:05:23.59,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,We're fighting each other because \Nwe can't forgive each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.09,0:05:27.98,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,And I mean, if we could forgive each \Nother, we wouldn't have to fight...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.63,0:05:30.33,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,So that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.07,0:05:37.04,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Even {\i1}I {\i0}have no idea what I'm trying to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.04,0:05:39.46,main,noelle,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you get for thinking \Nso hard when you're so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.46,0:05:41.05,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call me stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.05,0:05:44.46,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Then again, Captain Yami \Ntold me the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.46,0:05:46.61,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,All right! At times like this,\N I need to work out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.61,0:05:48.12,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,First, my abs!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.20,0:05:51.62,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Next, my back muscles!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.01,0:05:53.24,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,You meathead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.75,0:05:57.63,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's cramping at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.63,0:05:58.86,main,Yuno,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.63,0:06:03.12,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Yuno! Mimosa and Mr. Glasses, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.12,0:06:06.13,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come to visit Fuegoleon, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.13,0:06:08.14,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,No, we're here for another reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.14,0:06:14.30,top,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,The Golden Dawn had the most members pass \Nthe Royal Knights Entrance Exam, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.42,0:06:10.86,main,Mimosa,0000,0000,0000,,Asta! Are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.73,0:06:14.30,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,No need to worry about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.30,0:06:16.85,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I've trained every single muscle in my body!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.03,0:06:19.48,top,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,We've been having fiery meetings with \NCaptain Mereoleona these past few days
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.85,0:06:19.48,main,Yuno,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing you haven't \Ntrained is your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.48,0:06:21.74,top,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,so we don't let anyone down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.48,0:06:22.82,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Yup, exactly! It's super weak!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.82,0:06:24.48,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't make fun of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.81,0:06:28.82,main,Yuno,0000,0000,0000,,If there's a spell to make someone smarter,\N could someone use it on Asta?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.82,0:06:30.75,main,Bell,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're so nice, Yuno!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.75,0:06:33.35,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make weird requests like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.02,0:06:36.26,main,Mimosa,0000,0000,0000,,I'm terribly sorry. I can't think of any.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.26,0:06:37.91,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm actually kinda disappointed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.23,0:06:39.81,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.81,0:06:43.17,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,We have a big battle ahead of us,\N and you show no sense of urgency.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.83,0:06:46.46,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,What if an enemy spy finds out our plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.41,0:06:48.67,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,A spy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.65,0:06:55.01,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,It's entirely plausible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.54,0:06:58.06,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,They were able to bribe the \NCaptain of the Purple Orcas
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.06,0:07:01.02,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,to help them out with their \Nattack on the royal capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.35,0:07:04.02,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,You can never be too cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.02,0:07:05.67,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.67,0:07:07.53,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,We've gotta be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.55,0:07:13.39,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,If you two are also heading to the \Nroyal capital, would you like a ride?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.39,0:07:14.78,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,On my vessel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.26,0:07:19.33,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, really? Awesome! Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.33,0:07:21.96,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you insist...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.21,0:07:28.21,sign_10111_106_Venue_for_the_Ro,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Royal Capital\N{\fs30}Lodging House
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.78,0:07:28.21,top,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,So good!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.21,0:07:30.47,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,So good! So good!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.09,0:07:34.72,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,The food in the royal capital \Nis on another level!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.42,0:07:36.22,main,Mimosa,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.66,0:07:39.26,main,Mimosa,0000,0000,0000,,Asta, you have some sauce on your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.49,0:07:43.15,main,Mimosa,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me! I'm being too forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.15,0:07:44.61,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Mimosa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.61,0:07:46.43,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,You're eating entirely too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.43,0:07:48.59,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were going to be more cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.59,0:07:51.55,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah! Look at you, \Ngetting your mouth wiped like a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.55,0:07:55.18,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,N-Not that I care the slightest bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.18,0:07:57.67,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,But I am on my guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.67,0:08:00.41,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, I'd eat at least twice this much!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.10,0:08:04.70,main,Yuno,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.70,0:08:06.10,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.95,0:08:08.59,italics,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just Asta.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.59,0:08:13.02,italics,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,They may be talented, but there are \Na lot of troublemakers among them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.23,0:08:16.96,main,Luck,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait to fight some people!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.96,0:08:19.39,main,Luck,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna beat them to \Na pulp and squash them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.93,0:08:24.69,italics,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Zora is all by himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.05,0:08:28.44,italics,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,He must be too shy to talk to the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:30.94,italics,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,I need to be the one to break the ice!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.14,0:08:34.20,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.20,0:08:36.74,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,This is what your face looks like!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.79,0:08:44.28,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,It stinks so bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.28,0:08:46.04,main,Fragil,0000,0000,0000,,C-Captain Rill?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.27,0:08:53.55,main,Kirsch,0000,0000,0000,,All of you lack manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.31,0:08:58.87,main,Kirsch,0000,0000,0000,,Meals are meant to be enjoyed \Nin a much more elegant,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.87,0:09:01.69,main,Kirsch,0000,0000,0000,,beautiful, and distinguished fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.39,0:09:12.93,main,Kirsch,0000,0000,0000,,You dare run away from me because \Nyou don't want to be eaten?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.93,0:09:15.61,main,Kirsch,0000,0000,0000,,What a repulsive mushroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.61,0:09:17.31,main,Kirsch,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.89,0:09:20.49,main,Kirsch,0000,0000,0000,,You... repulsive... mushroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.49,0:09:23.29,main,Mush,0000,0000,0000,,Don't eat my brethren!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.63,0:09:31.04,main,Hamon,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, it appears that Miss Puli \Nwants to give us the gift of song.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.61,0:09:51.15,main,Puli,0000,0000,0000,,Puli, Puli, Puli, my skin's so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.15,0:09:54.90,top,Puli,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a lovely lady who sings so sweetly!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.49,0:09:54.90,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this song?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.90,0:09:59.03,top,Puli,0000,0000,0000,,Puli, Puli, Puli, I'm a lovely lady
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.38,0:09:58.33,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,How bad a singer can one be?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.33,0:10:01.20,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,As rude as this sounds,\N I want to murder someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.03,0:10:03.36,top,Puli,0000,0000,0000,,with supple cheeks!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.20,0:10:03.26,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.36,0:10:07.12,top,Puli,0000,0000,0000,,Puli poo pariponpen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.87,0:10:08.19,italics,Spy,0000,0000,0000,,I can't get any useful information \Nwhile I'm sticking to that guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.12,0:10:11.13,top,Puli,0000,0000,0000,,Pushka, pushka...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.82,0:10:22.45,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, \NCaptain of the Silver Eagles?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.97,0:10:26.14,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,You're taking three days \Nto start this operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.14,0:10:27.73,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,You're being awfully cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.42,0:10:29.87,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,What are you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.37,0:10:32.44,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I'm hesitating?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.85,0:10:37.40,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,No. It appears I needn't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.71,0:10:40.57,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,You always were perceptive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.45,0:10:46.89,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,I set a trap to find out how much \Nthe enemy knows of our plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.95,0:10:50.17,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.95,0:10:54.59,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Did you really think you could \Ntrick me with such a foolish spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.79,0:11:02.43,main,Spy,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.17,0:11:09.73,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,You're not getting away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.94,0:11:20.17,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,A spy from the Eye of the Midnight Sun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.17,0:11:22.49,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe there really was one...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.87,0:11:24.83,main,Mush,0000,0000,0000,,Mushroom is shocked!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.31,0:11:26.94,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Second-Place Rookie,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.94,0:11:29.83,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,apparently, he was following you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.02,0:11:33.51,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,To think I hadn't noticed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.51,0:11:34.96,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,How disgraceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.79,0:11:38.59,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,I questioned him without killing him,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.59,0:11:41.90,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,but apparently, our enemy hasn't \Nnoticed any of our movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.72,0:11:46.09,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, we will be moving up \Nthe operation's start time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.09,0:11:49.50,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,We strike the Eye of the Midnight \NSun's hideout tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.85,0:11:52.23,main,Fragil,0000,0000,0000,,T-Tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.23,0:11:54.19,main,Puli,0000,0000,0000,,Not in three days?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.53,0:11:58.36,main,Bell,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want Yuno to see \Nme right after I wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.21,0:12:01.95,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you all get plenty of rest tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.43,0:12:03.38,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.37,0:12:14.55,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It appears Lady Mereoleona intended \Nall along to depart immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.55,0:12:16.93,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,as soon as she captured the enemy spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.86,0:12:21.79,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,So if you want to fool your enemies, \Nyou must first fool your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.79,0:12:24.89,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But tomorrow morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.02,0:12:29.02,main,Zora,0000,0000,0000,,What a scary lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.93,0:12:35.11,main,Zora,0000,0000,0000,,What's up, shitty shrimp junior?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.11,0:12:36.69,main,Zora,0000,0000,0000,,You scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.07,0:12:39.69,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,It's the exact opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.93,0:12:43.45,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,The reason I want to become Wizard King
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.45,0:12:45.48,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,is so that everyone who lives here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.48,0:12:49.22,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,can have a free country \Nwhere they can always smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.62,0:12:54.19,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to stop their rampage,\N no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.19,0:12:56.71,main,Yuno,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better not go on a \Nrampage and hold us back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.14,0:12:59.34,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm never going to lose to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.63,0:13:02.01,main,Yuno,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who's going to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.05,0:13:04.34,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.34,0:13:05.34,main,Mimosa,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.07,0:13:09.47,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow is when we finally settle this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.85,0:13:10.97,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.46,0:13:13.71,main,All,0000,0000,0000,,...defeat the Eye of the Midnight Sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.04,0:13:43.07,sign_10111_106_Venue_for_the_Ro,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(1028,1)}Gravito Stones Floating Dungeon\N{\fs30}The Eye of the Midnight Sun's Hideout
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.18,0:13:43.07,top,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Holy crap! There's a castle \Nfloating in the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.07,0:13:46.42,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Eye of the \NMidnight Sun's hideout.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.97,0:13:54.14,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there aren't many who would \Nset foot in the strong magic regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.11,0:13:59.08,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,And since it's hidden by this \Nmagical fog, it's even harder to spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.08,0:14:01.40,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone would have difficulty finding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.15,0:14:05.78,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,You figured all that out, and that's \Nwhy you had people search this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.78,0:14:10.03,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotten better, \NCaptain of the Silver Eagles.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.03,0:14:12.91,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,I just happened to have \Npeople searching dungeons,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:16.25,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,and we coincidentally found \Nout it was their hideout.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.25,0:14:21.00,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? So what brought the Captain of \Nthe Silver Eagles himself here, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.17,0:14:24.75,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough idle chatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.45,0:14:28.26,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,You can use your spell from \Nthis distance, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.26,0:14:29.33,main,Shiren,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.86,0:14:47.28,main,Shiren,0000,0000,0000,,Stone Creation Magic: \NStone Model of the World.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.28,0:14:49.41,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,That's so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.41,0:14:53.61,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It's like an ants' nest that \Nallows entry from anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.61,0:14:55.79,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Seems simple enough to infiltrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.90,0:15:00.62,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,I see there are plenty of guys \Naround Senior Magic Knight level.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.34,0:15:04.77,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone with very \Npowerful magic in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.77,0:15:06.77,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Must be their boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.91,0:15:10.68,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,So that's where Licht is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.06,0:15:14.10,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Captain Nozel, what is our plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.10,0:15:17.25,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,I am not the Captain of the Royal Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.81,0:15:20.08,main,nozel,0000,0000,0000,,The one who'll decide that is Mereoleona.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.08,0:15:21.77,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.49,0:15:23.99,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up, all of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.99,0:15:27.03,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,If we want to ambush the enemy and \Nthrow them into a state of chaos,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.43,0:15:29.98,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,we can't let them know \Nhow many of us there are,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.98,0:15:32.51,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,so splitting up is the best option.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.10,0:15:36.38,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,But the fact that there are so many entrances
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.38,0:15:39.48,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,means that the enemy is \Nconfident in their defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.48,0:15:43.79,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,The more we split up, the more that \Nmay work against us and overwhelm us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.79,0:15:46.67,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,So where does that lead us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.67,0:15:47.77,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh, me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.77,0:15:51.34,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,We'll overwhelm the enemy even \Nmore with sheer willpower!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.89,0:15:55.35,main,Yuno,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need willpower. \NI'll overwhelm them myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.35,0:15:58.60,main,Luck,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna mash them all up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.38,0:16:03.28,main,Kirsch,0000,0000,0000,,I shall defeat them beautifully on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.28,0:16:04.85,main,Mimosa,0000,0000,0000,,I wish you'd just disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.85,0:16:06.90,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surrounded by idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.90,0:16:08.67,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,What's important is balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.75,0:16:13.78,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,The most effective way to get through \Nthe enemy's defense while split up
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.78,0:16:16.72,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,is to divide into five teams of four.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.72,0:16:18.28,main,Klaus,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you're thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.28,0:16:19.70,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.47,0:16:23.25,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,We will now split up into \Nfive groups and proceed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.64,0:16:28.12,main,Zora,0000,0000,0000,,I'll settle for anyone, as long as I don't \Nend up with the crazy stupid shrimp.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.12,0:16:33.81,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?! That's {\i1}my{\i0} line, \Nyou cool masked jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.53,0:16:35.53,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.53,0:16:38.74,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,No one would want to team up with you anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.74,0:16:41.34,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't mind teaming \Nup with you after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.34,0:16:45.23,main,Zora,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you sound like you're taking \Npity on me, you little shit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.23,0:16:49.48,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,You're coming with me, \Nyou damn problem children.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.18,0:16:51.71,main,Zora,0000,0000,0000,,Hello there, Lady Royal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.71,0:16:55.78,main,Zora,0000,0000,0000,,Please accept this rainbow stinkbug \Nas a token of our friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.78,0:16:56.69,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.37,0:17:04.63,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,A stench this weak has no effect on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.82,0:17:12.10,main,Zora,0000,0000,0000,,You sure you want two peasants \Nhanging around you, Lady Royal?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.10,0:17:14.51,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You're a peasant, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.51,0:17:17.56,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if you're a peasant or royalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.56,0:17:20.79,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,I've never given a rat's ass \Nabout differences in status.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.79,0:17:23.14,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,All that matters is if you're weak or strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.90,0:17:26.39,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,You're here because you're strong,\N are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.46,0:17:30.79,italics,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,The fools that Yami selected...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.58,0:17:33.99,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.99,0:17:35.32,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.32,0:17:39.74,main,Zora,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing. Guess I'll \Nbe careful, Lady Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.11,0:17:43.55,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of you should also be proud \Nto be chosen as Royal Knights,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.55,0:17:45.90,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,and use your strengths to the fullest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.59,0:17:49.38,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,I will now assign your positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:54.76,sign_25640_274_Group_1_En_Ringa,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Group 1\N{\fs20}En Ringard   Nils Ragus   Nozel Silva   Shiren Tium
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.30,0:17:52.89,top,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Group 1 will attack from the upper left.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.89,0:17:53.96,top,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.96,0:17:54.76,top,Shiren,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.76,0:17:59.01,sign_25640_274_Group_1_En_Ringa,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Group 2\N{\fs20}Ben Benfunk   Luck Voltia   Noelle Silva   Kirsch Vermillion
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.50,0:17:57.26,top,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Group 2 will attack from the lower left.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.26,0:17:58.26,top,Luck,0000,0000,0000,,'Kay!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.26,0:17:58.26,top,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.01,0:18:02.51,sign_25640_274_Group_1_En_Ringa,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Group 3\N{\fs20}Ruben Shagger   Rill Boismortier   Fragil Tormenta   Puli Angel
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.38,0:18:01.57,top,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Group 3 will attack from the upper right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.57,0:18:02.51,top,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.51,0:18:04.74,top,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Group 4 will attack from the lower right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.51,0:18:05.77,sign_25640_274_Group_1_En_Ringa,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Group 4 \N{\fs20}Klaus Lunettes   Mimosa Vermillion   Yuno   Hamon Caseus
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.74,0:18:05.77,top,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.77,0:18:12.27,sign_25640_274_Group_1_En_Ringa,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Group 5\N{\fs20}Asta   Mereoleona Vermillion   Zora Ideale
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.86,0:18:10.08,top,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,And we're going to attack front and center.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.08,0:18:10.98,top,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.87,0:18:15.03,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,The spatial magic user will stand by here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.50,0:18:18.03,main,Cob,0000,0000,0000,,Roger-dodger-roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.62,0:18:20.78,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better put your all into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.14,0:18:22.21,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.47,0:18:37.76,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why you're in this mess?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.70,0:18:43.86,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you're a citizen \Nof the Clover Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.10,0:18:49.19,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I was a citizen there myself, \Nuntil not so long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.19,0:18:50.31,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.01,0:18:53.31,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.99,0:19:00.16,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Licht gave me my true name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.13,0:19:08.87,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We're special, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.97,0:19:17.99,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,So we can do whatever we \Nwant to trash like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.58,0:19:29.41,main,Luck,0000,0000,0000,,He's way too weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.41,0:19:31.74,main,Luck,0000,0000,0000,,There are stronger guys, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.74,0:19:35.82,main,Kirsch,0000,0000,0000,,Do leave me some chances \Nto strike beautifully.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.25,0:19:37.80,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.80,0:19:39.41,main,Lady,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.73,0:19:45.02,flashback,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you don't need detailed plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.71,0:19:48.87,flashback,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Take down any enemies you encounter \Nas you proceed toward the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.50,0:19:50.62,flashback,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,You may do that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.62,0:19:53.02,flashback,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,however you prefer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.94,0:19:59.13,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care what you do \Nas long as you don't lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.10,0:20:04.54,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the ants show themselves at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.42,0:20:14.15,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you caused quite a mess at \Nthe royal capital while I was away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.86,0:20:20.90,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,You will not escape like you \Ndid from a certain cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.29,0:20:24.39,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,Eye of the Midnight Sun, we've come...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.39,0:20:25.62,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,...to get our revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.62,0:20:29.66,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you do that to my rival...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.66,0:20:31.70,main,Mere,0000,0000,0000,,To my foolish little brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.37,0:20:34.54,main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,You shall pay dearly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.03,0:20:37.96,main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,I will be the one to take your leader's head!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.46,0:20:42.89,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,H-Holy crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.89,0:20:44.97,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, do we even need to be here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.02,0:20:54.55,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like someone dangerous showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.55,0:20:56.98,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,Licht is gone right now, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.05,0:21:04.41,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I shouldn't be so lazy \Nabout this and just go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.00,0:22:40.50,sign_33083_276_Petit_Clover_,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,520)}Pe{\c&H3BC020&}t{\c&HE2AF0F&}i{\c&H3BC020&}t C{\c&HE2AF0F&}l{\c&H3BC020&}o{\c&H0E42D4&}ve{\c&H3BC020&}r
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.66,0:22:39.43,main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Petit Clover!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.00,0:22:44.00,sign_33188_278_The_Mystery_of_t,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(520,1)}Lazy Raia!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.06,0:22:42.87,main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Lazy Raia!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.00,0:22:46.19,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Raia! Lord Raia!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.97,0:22:50.01,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,What's up? Why are you so panicked?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.01,0:22:51.21,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We're being attacked!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.21,0:22:53.19,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.19,0:22:56.66,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,But it's such a pain to deal with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.66,0:22:58.49,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Please don't be like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.49,0:23:00.02,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pain to get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.37,0:23:01.69,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I shall sit you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.69,0:23:04.19,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pain to put shoes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.19,0:23:05.71,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I shall do that, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.35,0:23:08.36,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pain to stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.36,0:23:09.53,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Up you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.38,0:23:14.18,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,Walking is a huge pain! \NYeah, I'm not gonna do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.18,0:23:15.12,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.12,0:23:16.94,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Please reconsider!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.83,0:23:22.65,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,I think I was sleeping with my mouth open,\N because my throat hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.65,0:23:24.13,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you this lollipop!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.45,0:23:25.88,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,What flavor is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.88,0:23:27.88,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,A-Apple...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.42,0:23:33.39,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I shouldn't be so \Nlazy about this and just go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.58,0:23:37.26,main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What would've happened if \Nit was an orange lollipop?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.70,0:23:43.82,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I wonder how \NValtos and the others are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.82,0:23:48.64,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on {\i1}Black Clover{\i0}, Page 89:\N"The Black Bulls Hideout."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.11,0:23:54.25,sign_34238_338_Page_2_The_Boys_,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(234,1)}Page 89\N\N{\fs18} The Black Bulls Hideout
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.64,0:23:51.95,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you find what \Nwe're looking for, Val.
